      "question": "A charitable trust is distributing food packets to two different groups of people during a community event. Group A has $468$ people and Group B has $396$ people. The organizer wants to pack the food in such a way that each packet contains an equal number of items, and every person receives exactly one pack, with no leftovers in either group. To ensure efficiency, the organizer uses Euclid's division algorithm to determine the largest possible number of items ($k$) that can be placed in each pack such that the packets are uniform for both groups.",
